Follow strict coding standards:

- Adhere to PEP8 for code formatting.
- Follow PEP257 for docstring conventions.
- Use 4 spaces per indentation level (no tabs).
- Keep lines within 88 characters whenever possible.
- Use `snake_case` for variables and functions.
- Use `PascalCase` for class names.
- Use `UPPER_CASE_WITH_UNDERSCORES` for constants.
- Every function and class must have full type annotations.
- Every function and class must have a descriptive docstring.
- Always update outdated docstrings when modifying existing code.
- Preserve and respect all existing comments.
- Write AI-friendly code with clear naming and descriptive comments.

